{"html":"<!-- TITLE: Coding Convention --><!-- SUBTITLE: A quick summary of Coding Convention --><html><head></head><body><h1 id=\"import-export-constructor-proper-declaration\"><a class=\"toc-anchor nc-icon-outline location_bookmark-add internal-link\" href=\"#import-export-constructor-proper-declaration\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></a> Import / Export / Constructor proper declaration</h1>\n<h2 id=\"constructor\"><a class=\"toc-anchor nc-icon-outline location_bookmark-add internal-link\" href=\"#constructor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></a> Constructor</h2><div class=\"indent-h2\"><p>Always remove the auto generated console.log of ionic</p><p><strong>1 line</strong></p><pre class=\"hljs\"><code><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">constructor</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\"> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">public</span> navCtrl: NavController </span>) {}\n</code></pre><p><strong>2 or more lines</strong></p><pre class=\"hljs\"><code>  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">constructor</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\">\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">public</span> navCtrl: NavController,\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">public</span> navParams: NavParams,\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">public</span> imageViewerCtrl: ImageViewerController,\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">public</span> modalCtrl: ModalController\n  </span>) { }\n</code></pre></div>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"import-export\"><a class=\"toc-anchor nc-icon-outline location_bookmark-add internal-link\" href=\"#import-export\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></a> Import / Export</h2><div class=\"indent-h2\"><p><strong>1 line</strong></p><pre class=\"hljs\"><code> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">import</span> { IonicPage } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\">&apos;ionic-angular&apos;</span>;\n</code></pre><p><strong>2 or more lines</strong></p><pre class=\"hljs\"><code>    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">import</span> {\n        IonicPage,\n        NavController,\n        NavParams,\n        ModalController\n    } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\">&apos;ionic-angular&apos;</span>;\n\n</code></pre></div>\n\n\n\n\n<h1 id=\"line-spacing\"><a class=\"toc-anchor nc-icon-outline location_bookmark-add internal-link\" href=\"#line-spacing\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></a> Line Spacing</h1>\n<p><strong>2 lines</strong> away for every function</p>\n<p><img src=\"/uploads/drawisland.png\" alt=\"Drawisland\" title=\"Drawisland\"></p>\n<h1 id=\"classes\"><a class=\"toc-anchor nc-icon-outline location_bookmark-add internal-link\" href=\"#classes\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></a> Classes</h1>\n<p>Do use <strong>upper camel case</strong> when naming classes.</p>\n<p>Why? Follows conventional thinking for class names.<br>\nWhy? Classes can be instantiated and construct an instance. By convention, upper camel case indicates a constructable asset.</p>\n<pre class=\"hljs\"><code><span class=\"hljs-comment\">/* bad */</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span> exceptionService {\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">constructor</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\"></span>) { }\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">/* good */</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">class</span> ExceptionService {\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">constructor</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\"></span>) { }\n}\n\n</code></pre>\n<h1 id=\"constants\"><a class=\"toc-anchor nc-icon-outline location_bookmark-add internal-link\" href=\"#constants\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></a> Constants</h1>\n<p>Do declare variables with const if their values should not change during the application lifetime.<br>\n*   Why? Conveys to readers that the value is invariant.</p>\n<pre class=\"hljs\"><code><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> nationalHero = <span class=\"hljs-string\">&apos;Jose Rizal&apos;</span>;\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> heroesUrl = <span class=\"hljs-string\">&apos;api/heroes&apos;</span>;   \n</code></pre>\n</body></html>","meta":{"title":"Coding Convention","subtitle":"A quick summary of Coding Convention","path":"coding-convention"},"tree":[{"content":"Import / Export / Constructor proper declaration","anchor":"import-export-constructor-proper-declaration","nodes":[{"content":"Constructor","anchor":"constructor","nodes":[]},{"content":"Import / Export","anchor":"import-export","nodes":[]}]},{"content":"Line Spacing","anchor":"line-spacing","nodes":[]},{"content":"Classes","anchor":"classes","nodes":[]},{"content":"Constants","anchor":"constants","nodes":[]}],"parent":false}